==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Strabismus
<hw>Stra*bis"mus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/, fr. <?/ to squint, fr. <?/ distorted, squinting.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An affection of one or both eyes, in which the
optic axes can not be directed to the same object, -- a defect due
either to undue contraction or to undue relaxation of one or more of the
muscles which move the eyeball; squinting; cross-eye.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strabotomy</ent>⟦br⟧
